			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	&nbsp;</p>
<h2>
	fiveonenine games</h2>
<br />
<p>
	Dedicated to quickly becoming one of the top social mobile/web publishers, <a href="http://www.fiveoneninegames.com/" rel="nofollow">fiveonenine games</a> is the social entertainment joint venture of two leading media companies, The E.W. Scripps Company and Capitol Broadcasting.&nbsp; Based in beautiful North Carolina, fiveonenine entertains, engages and enlightens its audience by delivering a unique social experience that will forever change the gaming landscape.&nbsp; While fiveonenine is a relatively new entrant to the social gaming space, its parent companies bring almost 200 years of experience entertaining the mass market, and fiveonenine itself boasts a strong (and rapidly expanding) team of core and social game thought leaders.</p>
<p>
	&nbsp;</p>
<h2>
	Job Description</h2>
<br />
<p>
	fiveonenine games is seeking a smart and energetic Monetization expert (final level of this position will be determined based on the applicant&#39;s education, skills and experience)&nbsp; to join its quickly growing social games team!&nbsp; The successful candidate excels at deconstructing moment-to-moment gameplay and creating fun while providing options for monetization.&nbsp; The position will develop and refine the game economy while collaborating with key decision makers on new game features. They will be responsible for working with our product development teams to decide how the virtual economy is structured and optimized in every mobile and web social game.</p>
<p>
	&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	The successful individual will bring a deep sense of personal responsibility and accountability, along with drive, intelligence and passion both for and about analytics. He or she approaches work with a flexible and adaptable attitude toward changes in the business environment and the technology universe. The successful individual has proven his or her ability to work through conflict, build trust, and influence outcomes through outstanding interpersonal skills with all kinds of people at all levels.</p>
<p>
	&nbsp;</p>
<h2>
	Responsibilities of the Monetization position:</h2>
<br />
<ul>
	<br />
	<li>
		Develop monetization strategy and oversee day-to-day revenue management for free-to-play mobile games</li>
	<br />
	<li>
		Apply principles of behavioral economics and consumer psychology to fiveonenine&#39;s games</li>
	<br />
	<li>
		Manage sales and in-game economy data, categorize and maintain in-game virtual items</li>
	<br />
	<li>
		Work closely with game design and production teams to develop new monetization methods early in game development</li>
	<br />
	<li>
		Collaborate with marketing to create in-game promotions and define product updates that constantly introduce new revenue-generating initiatives</li>
	<br />
	<li>
		Collaborate with analytics to monitor and improve key performance metrics such as virality, engagement, and player lifetime value</li>
	<br />
	<li>
		Monitor key metrics on a daily and even hourly basis, react appropriately</li>
	<br />
	<li>
		Keep abreast of competitors games, particularly focusing on new monetization strategies</li>
	<br />
	<li>
		Promote a culture of collaboration, accountability, innovation, entrepreneurship, and overall excellence</li>
	<br />
</ul>
<br />
<h2>
	Job Requirements:</h2>
<br />
<p>
	The ideal candidate will have a love for consumer behavior. Specifically, the ideal candidate&#39;s background, experience, and skill set should include:</p>
<p>
	&nbsp;</p>
<ul>
	<br />
	<li>
		BA in Behavioral Economics or related field, MA or Phd preferred</li>
	<br />
	<li>
		Expert understanding of established monetization methods and desire to constantly innovate and define new methods</li>
	<br />
	<li>
		Strong analytic skills, a love for diving into the numbers</li>
	<br />
	<li>
		Experience with metrics driven-decision making</li>
	<br />
	<li>
		Extensive experience with Facebook and iOS games marketplaces, trends and best practices, preferred</li>
	<br />
	<li>
		Thorough experience with micro-transactional or free-to-pay based business models</li>
	<br />
	<li>
		Must have exceptional interpersonal communication skills and be willing to work in an extremely fast paced environment</li>
	<br />
	<li>
		Exceptionally self-motivated and directed</li>
	<br />
</ul>
<p>
	&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	&nbsp;</p>
<h2>
	ADDITIONAL INFORMATION</h2>
<br />
<ul>
	<br />
	<li>
		Candidates must be eligible to work in the United States</li>
	<br />
</ul>
<p>
	&nbsp;</p>
