	&nbsp;</p>
<h1>
	FiveOneNine Games</h1>
<br />
<p>
	Dedicated to quickly becoming one of the top social mobile/web publishers, FiveOneNine Games is the social entertainment joint venture of two leading media companies, The E.W. Scripps Company and Capitol Broadcasting.&nbsp; Based in beautiful North Carolina, FiveOneNine entertains, engages and enlightens its audience by delivering a unique social experience that will forever change the gaming landscape.&nbsp; While FiveOneNine is a relatively new entrant to the social gaming space, its parent companies bring almost 200 years of experience entertaining the mass market, and FiveOneNine itself boasts a strong (and rapidly expanding) team of core and social game thought leaders.<br />
	&nbsp;</p>
<h2>
	Job Description</h2>
<br />
<p>
	FiveOneNine games is seeking a Game Designer (level of this position will be determined based on the applicant&#39;s education, skills and experience) to join our quickly growing social games team! The successful candidate is insightful on social game dynamics from player experience to commercial design, is an adept communicator, and is very effective working in a team and independently. The candidate must have a passion for social games and be able to design intuitive user experience. The position collaborates with our producers and development teams to guide the creative elements of game production.</p>
<p>
	&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	&nbsp;</p>
<h2>
	Responsibilities of the position:</h2>
<ul>
	<li>
		Participate as a key member of the production team focused on creative elements to guide projects from concept to launch and beyond.</li>
	<li>
		Design clever and engaging game loops.</li>
	<li>
		Support producers throughout the product lifecycle with subject-matter-expertise on social game design, for one or several projects</li>
	<li>
		Review and give feedback on game design documents, builds, and plans</li>
	<li>
		Brainstorming and design work when development teams run into challenges and need additional creative assistance</li>
	<li>
		Work with others to originate ideas for new game projects</li>
	<li>
		Complete writing and narrative development tasks as needed</li>
</ul>
<p>
	&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	&nbsp;</p>
<h2>
	Job Requirements:</h2>
<ul>
	<li>
		Passionate about the social game space.</li>
	<li>
		Strong understanding of current design techniques to deliver excellent engagement, retention, and monetization. Can concisely articulate core social game loops.</li>
	<li>
		Experience designing F2P and/or micro-transaction-based published titles, and experience in design leadership.</li>
	<li>
		Strong creative and technical writing skills</li>
	<li>
		Exceptional interpersonal communication and collaboration skills.</li>
	<li>
		Exceptionally self-motivated and directed.</li>
	<li>
		Able to communicate easily in a visual manner.</li>
	<li>
		Good knowledge of the workings of social networks.</li>
	<li>
		Able to balance between innovation and setting reasonable goals.<br />
		&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<h2>
	ADDITIONAL INFORMATION</h2>
<br />
<ul>
	<li>
		Candidates must be eligible to work in the United States</li>
</ul>
<p>
	&nbsp;</p>
